      "content": "It's a risk that some traditional or very voluminous styles might be perceived as less business-like by those accustomed to a very specific, narrow standard of corporate presentation. The most authoritative look in a boardroom is one that signals immediate competence and adherence to established power structures, which often favors more subdued aesthetics. If a style draws too much attention away from the discussion, it can unfortunately be misinterpreted as a lack of seriousness by some observers.",
